{
  "analysis": "We are in /app as root. The user has built a kernel at /app/linux-6.9/arch/x86/boot/bzImage and wants an initramfs at /app/ramfs/initramfs.cpio.gz that boots to a login prompt on the serial console (ttyS0) under QEMU -nographic, with the ability to log in as root with no password. The simplest reliable approach is to build a minimal initramfs using a statically linked busybox, include an /init that mounts proc/sys/dev and hands off to busybox init, and configure /etc/inittab to spawn a getty on ttyS0 that runs /bin/login. We'll provide /etc/passwd and /etc/shadow with an empty root password, and include minimal device nodes (/dev/console, /dev/null, /dev/tty, /dev/ttyS0) to ensure early console works even if devtmpfs isn't auto-mounted. We'll pack it as a newc cpio and gzip it to the requested path.",
  "plan": "- Verify the kernel image path exists.\n- Install busybox-static and cpio (so we have a static busybox and tool to build the archive).\n- Create the initramfs directory structure under /app/ramfs/rootfs.\n- Copy the static busybox into the initramfs and create necessary symlinks for init, sh, getty, login.\n- Create /init script to mount proc, sys, and dev (devtmpfs if available) and exec busybox init.\n- Create /etc files: passwd, shadow (root with empty password), group, securetty, and inittab to spawn getty on ttyS0.\n- Create essential device nodes inside the initramfs.\n- Build the initramfs cpio.gz at /app/ramfs/initramfs.cpio.gz and list it.\n- The user can then run the provided qemu-system-x86_64 command to boot and log in as root with no password.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -l /app/linux-6.9/arch/x86/boot/bzImage\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /app/ramfs/rootfs/{bin,sbin,etc,proc,sys,dev,usr/bin,usr/sbin,root,tmp,dev/pts}\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get update\n",
      "duration": 40.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get install -y busybox-static cpio\n",
      "duration": 40.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cp -a /bin/busybox /app/ramfs/rootfs/bin/busybox\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ln -sf /bin/busybox /app/ramfs/rootfs/bin/sh && ln -sf /bin/busybox /app/ramfs/rootfs/sbin/init && ln -sf /bin/busybox /app/ramfs/rootfs/sbin/getty && ln -sf /bin/busybox /app/ramfs/rootfs/bin/login\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/ramfs/rootfs/init << 'EOF'\n#!/bin/sh\nset -eu\nexport PATH=/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin\n# Mount essential filesystems\nmount -t proc proc /proc || true\nmount -t sysfs sysfs /sys || true\n# Prefer devtmpfs if available, else ensure minimal nodes\nmount -t devtmpfs devtmpfs /dev 2>/dev/null || true\n[ -e /dev/console ] || mknod -m 600 /dev/console c 5 1\n[ -e /dev/null ]    || mknod -m 666 /dev/null    c 1 3\n[ -e /dev/tty ]     || mknod -m 666 /dev/tty     c 5 0\n[ -e /dev/ttyS0 ]   || mknod -m 600 /dev/ttyS0   c 4 64\nmkdir -p /dev/pts || true\nmount -t devpts devpts /dev/pts 2>/dev/null || true\n# Hand off to BusyBox init (reads /etc/inittab)\nexec /sbin/init\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chmod +x /app/ramfs/rootfs/init\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/ramfs/rootfs/etc/passwd << 'EOF'\nroot:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/sh\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/ramfs/rootfs/etc/shadow << 'EOF'\nroot::19000:0:99999:7:::\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chmod 600 /app/ramfs/rootfs/etc/shadow\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/ramfs/rootfs/etc/group << 'EOF'\nroot:x:0:\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/ramfs/rootfs/etc/securetty << 'EOF'\nttyS0\nconsole\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/ramfs/rootfs/etc/inittab << 'EOF'\n::sysinit:/bin/echo \"Initramfs starting...\"\nttyS0::respawn:/sbin/getty -L ttyS0 115200 vt100\n::ctrlaltdel:/bin/echo \"CTRL-ALT-DEL pressed\"\n::shutdown:/bin/umount -a -r\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mknod -m 600 /app/ramfs/rootfs/dev/console c 5 1 || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mknod -m 666 /app/ramfs/rootfs/dev/null c 1 3 || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mknod -m 666 /app/ramfs/rootfs/dev/tty c 5 0 || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mknod -m 600 /app/ramfs/rootfs/dev/ttyS0 c 4 64 || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "( cd /app/ramfs/rootfs && find . | cpio -H newc -o -R root:root | gzip -9 > /app/ramfs/initramfs.cpio.gz )\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /app/ramfs/initramfs.cpio.gz\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'To boot: qemu-system-x86_64 -kernel /app/linux-6.9/arch/x86/boot/bzImage -initrd /app/ramfs/initramfs.cpio.gz -append \"console=ttyS0\" -nographic'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

